## Maximizing Your Experience on a Shoestring

To truly enjoy Paris without breaking the bank, focus on the city's free outdoor spaces and strategic timing. The **Sacré-Cœur** offers breathtaking views at a fraction of the cost of the Eiffel Tower, while the **Luxembourg Gardens** provide a serene escape. By timing your museum visits correctly, you can access world-class art like the Impressionists at the **Musée d'Orsay** for free.

## Navigating the City Efficiently

Paris has one of the most efficient public transport systems in the world. Purchasing a **Navigo Easy** card allows for unlimited travel on the Metro and buses for a few days, costing significantly less than individual tickets. Combine this with extensive walking tours through historic neighborhoods like **Montmartre** and **Le Marais** to save money and immerse yourself in the local atmosphere.
